## Per-Image Workflows

Each image should have its own workflow file:
- Naming: `.github/workflows/<image-name>.yml`
- Trigger on relevant file changes only
- Use branch-based tagging (dev, latest, stable)
- Use reusable workflow: `.github/workflows/docker-build.yml`

### Workflow Structure

Standard pattern for image workflows:

```yaml
name: ğŸ³ <Image Name> Docker Image

on:
  push:
    branches: [master, dev]
    paths:
      - '.github/workflows/<image-name>.yml'
      - '.github/workflows/docker-build.yml'
      - 'images/<image-name>/**'
  pull_request:
    branches: [master, dev]
    paths:
      - '.github/workflows/<image-name>.yml'
      - '.github/workflows/docker-build.yml'
      - 'images/<image-name>/**'
  workflow_dispatch:
    inputs:
      version_var:
        description: 'Version description'
        required: false
        default: 'v1.0.0'
        type: string
      force_rebuild:
        description: 'Force rebuild without cache'
        required: false
        default: false
        type: boolean
      custom_tags:
        description: 'Additional custom tags (comma-separated, optional)'
        required: false
        default: ''
        type: string

jobs:
  build:
    uses: ./.github/workflows/docker-build.yml
    permissions:
      contents: read
      packages: write
      id-token: write
    with:
      image_name: jethome-dev-<image-name>
      context_path: images/<image-name>
      force_rebuild: ${{ github.event.inputs.force_rebuild == true }}
      custom_tags: ${{ github.event.inputs.custom_tags || '' }}
      build_args: |
        VERSION_VAR=${{ github.event.inputs.version_var || 'v1.0.0' }}
```

### Version Handling

- Put version defaults in `workflow_dispatch` input defaults
- Pass versions to Dockerfile via `build_args`
- Easy to override manually via GitHub UI

## Local Testing

Test workflows locally using `act`:
- Configuration in `.actrc`
- Test specific job: `act -j build`
- Use `.secrets` file for local secrets (gitignored)
